 Many thanks Jerry for the history lesson, and the Happy Thanksgiving. I did
indeed enjoy a great dinner created by my wife, Turkey, brussel sprouts,
glazed parnsips, stuffing, cranberry sauce, roasted potatoes, mixed carrots
and peas, and for Tony - A Canuck version of candied yams!! (Maybe not
Canuck, but def. delicious).



Cook your yams up (about 2-3 lbs) until they can be mashed.

Add about 1 generous Tb of fresh ground ginger (not powder)

Add about 1 generous Tb of dark brown sugar (or more to taste)

Add a splash of port or sherry (about 4 Tb should do it, or to taste)



Enjoy ginger mashed yams, you will love them, they are always fought over in
my house.



And here's an early Thanksgiving wish to my American friends and allies in
these tough times worldwide.



Blessings to all,



Courtney







 

