Hi Courtney and Tony (or Euell?),

 

I recently transplanted myself from the States to Canada and so had ocassion
to look up the history of "Thanksgiving". I'd like to toss into the mix that
the first North American "thanksgiving" celebration was celebrated by
Frobisher in Newfoundland in 1578, which puts him before even the Pilgrims.
Of course, there was no concept of "Canada" then, or the "United States"
either, so someone is going to argue that it doesn't count.

 

First, last, or also ran, I had a turkey dinner today, and it was darn good.
I hope you did too, Courtney. And you too, Tony, when the time comes and if
you're not watching football.

 

See you on the road,

Jerry

Galiano Island, BC

 

 


